Add a plugin system to the Forever library. Create a `src/plugins.js` module that allows users to register, unregister, and compose plugins that can hook into any Forever module's lifecycle. Requirements: 1) A `PluginManager` class with `register(name, plugin)`, `unregister(name)`, `getPlugin(name)`, and `listPlugins()` methods. 2) Each plugin is an object with optional lifecycle hooks: `beforeCall`, `afterCall`, `onError` — these hooks receive the function name and arguments/return value. 3) A `withPlugins(fn, pluginManager)` higher-order function that wraps any Forever module function so registered hooks fire automatically. 4) Plugins should support async hooks. 5) Include a built-in `loggingPlugin` example that logs every call with timestamps, and a `timingPlugin` that records execution time per call. 6) Add comprehensive tests covering hook ordering, async hooks, error hooks, and plugin composition. 7) Export everything cleanly from `src/index.js`.